Files in this program:
plagiarismCatcher.cpp

No makefile

Compile with:
g++ -o plagiarismCatcher plagiarismCacher.cpp

Example command to run:
./plagiarismCatcher path/to/files 6 200

where the first command line argument is the path to the files (uneccessary if folder containing the files is already with the executables),
first number is the chunk of number of word sequences being checked for plagiarism, and the second number is the minimum number of similarities
checked for

the files with more similarities than the second number given in the command line are listed in descending order of similarities

the files are listed with their path